                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            <p>عيون الهداية</p>
                            <p>This MS. was one of the five bought at Constantinople in May, 1901, at the
                                sale of a Bektashi dervish's effects, and is described under the heading "(24) C. 10
                                (Turkish)" on p. 31 (563) of Further Notes. It begins with about four pages of
                                Arabic (ff. 1-3) invoking blessings on the twelve Imáms, and then continues in
                                Turkish:</p>
                            <p>راقم تسويدات المنّان صحايف عصیان خریدی رسمی بکتاشی ناتوان بو طرزیله تحقیق بیان
                                حال و بو نهجیله شرح ما فى البال ايدرا</p>
                            <p>There are numerous quotations from the Qur'an and Traditions, and at least
                                one from the Gospels, and the reader is continually addressed Imdi, 'aziz-i-man
                                ("Now my dear Friend"). Author, Kiridi Rasmi-i-Bektáshi; copyist, Maḥmúd Bábá.</p>
                        </summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="E_15-item1">
                            <author key="person_305822301">
                                <persName xml:lang="tr">Kiridi Rasmi-i-Bektáshi</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="tr">Giridī ʿAlī Resmī, 18e</persName>
                            </author>
                            
                            <title xml:lang="ar">عيون الهداية</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="">'Uyūn al-Hidāya</title>
                            <incipit xml:lang="ota">راقم تسويدات المنّان صحايف عصیان خریدی رسمی
                                بکتاشی ناتوان بو طرزیله تحقیق بیان حال و بو نهجیله شرح ما فى البال
                                ايدرا</incipit>
